theorem Topology.interior_inter_closure_subset_closure_inter
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior A ∩ closure B ⊆ closure (A ∩ B) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hxIntA, hxClB⟩
  -- We will verify the neighbourhood criterion for `x` with respect to `A ∩ B`.
  have : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B) := by
    apply (mem_closure_iff).2
    intro V hVopen hxV
    -- Choose an open neighbourhood of `x` contained in `A`.
    rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hxIntA with
      ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsubA⟩
    -- Intersect the two neighbourhoods.
    have hVUopen : IsOpen (V ∩ U) := hVopen.inter hUopen
    have hxVU : x ∈ V ∩ U := ⟨hxV, hxU⟩
    -- Since `x ∈ closure B`, this neighbourhood meets `B`.
    have h_nonempty : ((V ∩ U) ∩ B).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClB (V ∩ U) hVUopen hxVU
    rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyV, hyU⟩, hyB⟩
    -- The point `y` lies in `A` because `U ⊆ A`.
    have hyA : y ∈ A := hUsubA hyU
    exact ⟨y, ⟨hyV, ⟨hyA, hyB⟩⟩⟩
  exact this
